{{Infobox dam | name = Baihetan Dam | image = | image_caption = | name_official = 白鹤滩大坝 | dam_crosses = [[Jinsha River]] | location = | dam_type = double-curvature [[arch dam]] | dam_length = | dam_height = {{convert|277|m|ft}} | dam_width_crest = {{convert|13|m|ft}} | dam_width_base = {{convert|72|m|ft}} | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | construction_began = 2008 | opening = 2021 (est.) | cost = $6.3 billion<ref>https://www.hydroworld.com/articles/2017/08/ctgc-begins-construction-on-the-16-gw-baihetan-hydropower-station-in-southwest-china.html</ref> | owner = | res_name = | res_capacity_total ={{Convert|17924000000|m3|acre.ft|0|abbr=on}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Baihetan Hydropower|url=http://www.bht.yn.gov.cn/Article/2007/20070915124026.html|publisher=Baihetan|accessdate=23 August 2011|language=Chinese}}</ref> | res_catchment = | res_surface = | res_max_depth = | plant_operator = | plant_turbines = 16 × 1,000 [[Megawatt|MW]] | plant_capacity = 16,000 MW | plant_annual_gen = 60.24 TWh<ref name="cwe"/> | plant_commission = | plant_decommission = | location_map = China | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|27|12|13|N|102|53|59|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | website = | extra = }} The '''Baihetan Dam''' ({{zh|s=白鹤滩大坝|t=白鶴灘大壩|p=Báihètān Dàbà}}) is a large [[hydroelectric dam]] under construction on the [[Jinsha River]], a tributary of the [[Yangtze River]] in [[Sichuan]] and [[Yunnan]] provinces, in the southwest of [[People's Republic of China|China]]. The dam is a 277 m tall double-curvature [[arch dam]] with a crest elevation of 827 m. Its width will be 72 m at the base and 13 m at the crest.<ref name="cwe"/>
The facility will generate power by utilizing 16 [[water turbine|turbines]], each with a generating capacity of {{nowrap|1,000 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, taking the generating capacity to {{nowrap|16,000 MW}}.<ref>http://www.dongfang.com/data/v/201507/4714.html</ref> In terms of generating capacity, it will be the second largest [[hydroelectric]] power plant in the world, after the [[Three Gorges Dam]].<ref>http://news.bjx.com.cn/html/20151202/687530.shtml</ref> When finished, it will be the third largest dam in [[China]] and the [[List of largest dams|fourth in the world]], in terms of dam volume. Construction on the dam began in 2008 and is expected to be complete in 2021.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Brief History of Hydropower Development Baihetan |url=http://nn.lsz.gov.cn/lry.asp?id=164 |publisher=Baihetan China - Ningxia County Public Information Network |accessdate=20 March 2011 |language=Chinese |date=2 December 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110823083909/http://nn.lsz.gov.cn/lry.asp?id=164 |archivedate=23 August 2011 |df= }}</ref> {{clear}}
