The '''Marduk-zakir-shumi I kudurru''' is a boundary stone ([[kudurru]]) of [[Marduk-zakir-šumi I]], a king in the [[List of kings of Babylon#Dynasty IX of Babylon|10th dynasty]] of [[Babylon]] from 855 - 819 BC.

The kudurru of Marduk-zakir-shumi is a [[stele]]-like kudurru, with a front face of [[Cuneiform script|cuneiform]], and a semi-circular top, (a [[Register (sculpture)|register]] area), with the king, people, and [[Iconography|iconographic]] representations of gods.

